  "text": "Notably, it was not necessary to distinguish between individual afferents or to weigh their contribution according to their position in the hair field. Hence, our model shows that there is no need for labelled lines or somatotopy in this sensory system. Instead, simple summation of hair field activity is sufficient to explain the coding properties of position-sensitive DINs. In contrast, the position of antennal contacts along the flagellum was proposed to be encoded by a labelled-line principle [CITATION_1] .",
